CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. A19 reads: "B'nai B'rith Gives Library - Student Robert Vearnon accepts the first volume of a vocational library presented to Fifth Ave. High School by B'nai B'rith on Feb. 10. Taking part in ceremonies are, left to right: Mrs. Maurice Slutsky, president, B'nai B'rith Women's Council of Greater Pittsburgh; F. Gardner Gillen, principal of Fifth Ave. High; Vearnon, and Mrs. Herman Mogerman.  B'nai B'rith Council Vocational Service. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Mrs. Maurice Slutsky, Principal F. Gardner Gillen, Robert Vearnon, and Mrs. Herman Mogerman, gathered during B'nai B'rith's presentation of vocational library to Fifth Avenue High School
